{"id": "1510443491107536976", "channel_id": "1510443491107536976", "author_id": "277927692735873035", "author_name": "sacred_promises", "content": "hi, this is quality of life suggestion to make damage text in the game visually “clearer” to show the source of damage done. \n\nfor example, damage types like corrosion, bleed, poison, sacrifice, final verdict all have their own unique symbol when applied onto an enemy however, when they trigger, the damage text shown are all the same, in the default red text. \n\nthis can be especially confusing visually, in cases like when multi hits are performed on a target with corrosion, there is no visual indicator to differentiate active damage vs damage from corrosion stacks.\n\nperhaps the damage done by these effects could be in a different color? or have their unique symbol beside the corresponding damage number like when they are applied.", "timestamp": "2026-05-31T00:43:10.963000+00:00", "thread_id": "1510443491107536976", "reactions": [{"emoji": "Ogier_Cheerup", "emoji_id": "1468259351889318049", "count": 2}]}
